From Michael Covington Subject Re food related seizures I'm told that corn allergy is fairly common My wife has it and it seems to be exacerbated if sugar is eaten with the corn I suppose that in a person just on the verge of having epilepsy, an allergic reaction might cause a seizure, but I don't really know Gordon Michael A Covington, Associate Research Scientist Artificial Intelligence Programs The University of Georgia phone Athens, Georgia U S A amateur radio N TMI